Euro Crisis Resolution Measures Carry High Risk, Katainen Says

-- B y   K a t i   P o h j a n p a l o
-- 
2011-09-20T12:03:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-20/euro-crisis-resolution-measures-carry-high-risk-katainen-says.html
All alternatives for ending the
crisis in the euro area carry a high risk,  Finland ’s Prime
Minister  Jyrki Katainen  said.  “There is no cost-free option for solving the euro
crisis,” Katainen told lawmakers in the Helsinki-based
parliament today. “We are doing all we can to ensure the
survival of the euro.”  Bailouts have stopped a “total” collapse of the single
currency even as the debt problem remains, Katainen said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kati Pohjanpalo at 
 kpohjanpalo@bloomberg.net  